### Step 3 – Translate core data models and project persistence

**Objective**  
Translate **project and editor state** from TypeScript types and JSON persistence into Swift models and save/load paths, **without** extending the schema with new fields for “nice to have” ideas.

**What to translate**

- **Electron references:** [`old-electron/src/components/video-editor/projectPersistence.ts`](../old-electron/src/components/video-editor/projectPersistence.ts) (`EditorProjectData`, load/save), [`old-electron/src/components/video-editor/types.ts`](../old-electron/src/components/video-editor/types.ts) (`ZoomRegion`, `SpeedRegion`, trim, annotations, cursor types, etc.).
- **Behaviors to preserve:** `.recordly` (or equivalent) project semantics: version, paths to assets, in-project editor state (zoom regions, trim, speed, annotations, audio, crop, webcam, captions, aspect ratio, export defaults, cursor settings) as described in [`behaviors.md`](./behaviors.md).
- **Constraint:** Field-level parity with the **existing** fork; new concepts belong in a post-parity phase.

**Status:** Non démarré

